item.name: DE
Implicit Sequence
item.description:
An implicit sequence example for a hotel booking transaction flow

1. Reservation for 1 night (not cancellable) -> info-internal + info-order (1.1 Info internal, 1.2 Info order)
2. Checkin -> FULL PAYMENT -> pos-receipt (2. Pos Receipt)
3. Consumption 1 beer at the bar -> room charge -> info-order (3. Info Order)
4. Purchase of a greeting card -> payed immediately -> pos-receipt (4. Pos Receipt)
5. Checkout -> Payment of consumption from 3 -> pos-receipt (5. Pos Receipt)

item.name: Explicit Sequence
item.description:
An explicit sequence example for a hotel booking transaction flow

1. Reservation for 1 night (not cancellable) -> info-internal + info-order (1.1.1 Info internal (Start transaction), 1.1.2 Info internal (Finish transaction), 1.2.1 Info order (Start transaction), 1.2.2 Info order (Finish transaction))
2. Checkin -> FULL PAYMENT -> pos-receipt (2.1 Pos Receipt (Start transaction), 2.2 Pos Receipt (Finish transaction))
3. Consumption of 1 beer at the bar -> room charge -> info-order (3.1 Info Order (Start transaction), 3.2 Info Order (Finish transaction))
4. Purchase of a greeting card -> payed immediately -> pos-receipt (4.1 Pos Receipt (Start transaction), 4.2 Pos Receipt (Finish transaction))
5. Checkout -> Payment of consumption from 3 -> pos-receipt (5.1 Pos Receipt (Start transaction), 5.2 Pos Receipt (Finish transaction))
